rd\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf3 Inserted Reference\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 8 The Sabbath law showed Jehovah\u8217?s concern for both the physical and the spiritual welfare of his people. \u8220?The sabbath came into existence for the sake of man,\u8221? said Jesus. (Mark 2:27) It not only allowed the Israelites to rest but also gave them the opportunity to draw close to and show love for their Creator. (Deuteronomy 5:12) It was a day dedicated exclusively to spiritual interests. That included family worship, prayer, and meditation on God\u8217?s Law. The arrangement served to protect the Israelites from using all their time and energy in material pursuits. The Sabbath reminded them that their relationship with Jehovah was the most important thing in their lives. Jesus reiterated that unchanging principle when he said: \u8220?It is written, \u8216?Man must live, not on bread alone, but on every utterance coming forth through Jehovah\u8217?s mouth.\u8217?\u8221?\u8212?Matthew 4:4.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 9 God\u8217?s people are no longer required to observe a literal 24-hour sabbath rest, but the Sabbath arrangement remains much more than a historical curiosity. (Colossians 2:16) Is it not a reminder that we too must give spiritual activities priority? Sacred interests must not be overshadowed by material preoccupations or recreational pursuits. (}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22\cf3 Hebrews 4:9, 1}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 0) So we might ask ourselves: \u8220?What takes first place in my life? Am I giving priority to study, prayer, attendance at Christian meetings, and the sharing of the good news of the Kingdom? Or are other interests crowding out such activities?\u8221? If we put spiritual matters first in our lives, Jehovah assures us that we will not lack the necessities of life.\u8212?Matthew 6:24-33.\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 10 Periods spent studying the Bible and related publications, as well as thinking deeply about their message, can help us to draw closer to Jehovah. (James 4:8) Susan, who some 40\u160?years ago began setting aside time for regular Bible study, acknowledges that at first it was not fun. It was a chore. But the more she read, the more she enjoyed it. Now she really misses her personal study if for some reason she cannot get to it. \u8220?Study has helped me to get to know Jehovah as a Father,\u8221? she says. \u8220?I can trust him, rely upon him, and freely approach him in prayer. It is really overwhelming to see how much Jehovah loves his servants, how he cares for me personally, and how he has acted in my behalf.\u8221? What great joy we too can have from regularly attending to our spiritual needs!\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf3 [End of meeting part.]\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\qc {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af1\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f2\cf4\b Living as Christians\par}\pard\plain\langnp1033\langfenp1033 \ltrpar\ql {\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 \u8226? Song 134\par}{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22 \u8226? }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ab\ai\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langnp1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\f3\fs22\b\i \u8220?Taught by Jehovah to Raise Our Family\u8221?: }{\rtlch\fcs1\alang1033\af0\afs22\ltrch\fcs0\lang1033\langn